, they realized this swarm of them was a bit larger than they were used to.
 Then a couple of mages got a strange headache at the most inconvenient of
 times and failed their spells, and some of the hook goblins managed to close
 into melee range…

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The defenders dissolved into chaos.
 The troops manning the defenses may have thought the attitude unfair, but
 there was a reason why the Ibasan leadership considered most of them to be the
 dregs of their invasion force.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The commanders of the force delayed asking for help as long as possible, afraid
 of what their superiors would say if they proved unable to contain even a
 simple hook goblin incursion.
 What a humiliation that would be!

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That changed when an entire regiment of steel golems came running into the gate
 chamber, following behind the last hook goblins.
